| image2 = The Cave Xalo Hossain Kokan.jpg | alt2 = | caption2 = A image from the stone cave of Hossein Kohkan }} '''Hossein Osmani''' ({{lang-ku|حوسێن عوسمانی|italic=no}} 28 September 1930 in [[Darvaleh-ye Pain]], [[Kermanshah province|Kermanshah]], [[Iran]] - 26 July 2016 in [[Banevreh]], [[Kermanshah province|Kermanshah]], [[Iran]]) also known as '''Khalo Hossein Kohkan''' ({{lang-ku|خاڵۆ حوسێن کۆکەن|translit=Xalo Husên Koken|italic=no}}) (in meaning Digging Mountain or Caveman) or '''Farhad the Second''' ({{lang-fa|فرهاد ثانی}}, {{lang|fa|فرهاد دوم}}) was an [[Iranian peoples|Iranian]] [[Kurds|Kurd]] who left his village 21 years ago and started carving cliff rocks on a mountain near [[Banevreh|Banevreh City]] Of functions [[Paveh County]] in the [[Kermanshah province]] in Iran. He carved seven rooms in a rocky mountain, as well as his own grave. He was given the title of Farhad II, a fictional figure in the Iranian literature who agreed to carve a mountain after his love-rival, one of the Iranian kings, sends him on exile.<ref name="te01">[http://rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iran/270720162 Hero of the KDPI Peshmerga, Hussein Koken, has died], [[Rudaw Media Network]].</ref><ref name="te02">[http://kurdpress.com/En/NSite/FullStory/News/?Id=13804 Kurdish man hand-carved own home passes away], KurdPress News Agency.</ref><ref name="te03">[http://basnews.com/index.php/en/news/middle-east/289585 Kurdish Caveman Dies After 21 Years of Solitude], BasNews.</ref><ref name="te04">[http://ir.voanews.com/a/hossein-koh-kan-obit/3436984.html حسین کوهکن یا فرهاد دوم کرمانشاه درگذشت], [[Voice of America]] (Persian).</ref><ref name="te05">[https://www.radiozamaneh.com/190172 شاهکار خالو حسین کوهکن «فرهاد دوم، خالق حقیقتی شبیه افسانه‌ها در دل کوه‌های اورامانات»], [[Radio Zamaneh]] (Persian).</ref><ref name="te06">[http://www.mehrnews.com/news/3723942/ فرهاد کوهکن زمانه درگذشت/ پایان داستان خالق غار سنگی], [[Mehr News Agency]] (Persian).</ref><ref name="te07">[http://www.destinati