'''Purian''' (also '''Purían''') is a pair of [[extinct language]]s of eastern [[Brazil]]:
*[[Purí language|Purí]] *[[Coroado Puri language|Coroado Puri]] (also known as Colorado)
[[Coropó language|Coropó]] (Koropó), once spoken in [[Minas Gerais]] and [[Rio de Janeiro (state)|Rio de Janeiro]], was added by Campbell (1997), but removed again by Ramirez et al. (2015).
Purian is part of the [[Macro-Jê]] proposal. However, when Coropó is removed, there are not sufficient lexical connections to maintain this classification.<ref name=Glottolog/>
